      "span_text": "However, loss of K + selectivity in KCNJ5 G151R and KCNJ5 L168R channels as well as loss of sensitivity to the K + channel blockers barium (7) and tertiapin-Q  suggest that the pore of mutant channels is sufficiently altered to enable small molecules to block ion passage through the mutant, but not the WT, channel."
